post_text:
Patriots,

In case you haven't heard, State Superintendent Kathy Hoffman released the attached statement in regards to schools reopening. There is a strong possibility that in person instruction will not resume by August 17. MALC/MAES will continue with its first five days of alternative instruction, as planned. This will include open house and Galileo assessments as previously scheduled.

We are awaiting further guidance and clarification from the State on August 7th. Thank you for your patience and understanding.

YEARBOOK UPDATE

Many of you have asked about yearbooks, so here's an update.

The elementary yearbook is done and shipping to the school. However, you can still go online and order as well and have it shipped to your home. There is a link on the front page of our website at https://mohavelearning.org.

The middle and high school yearbooks are being merged into a single MALC yearbook (like we did for years until recently). The price will remain at the $45 high school yearbook price. The new combo yearbook can still be purchase online on our website at the link listed above.

GRADUATION UPDATE

We recently announced that the upcoming high school graduation was being moved outdoors to The Battlefield at 10 am. However, in hope that the "stay-at-home" order will be lifted after April 30th and many in our community will be returning to the workplace, we are changing the date of the graduation to Saturday, May 9th.

We plan to mark off sections of the field for each family/small group to still provide some social distancing during the ceremony. We also realize that the community may not be ready for public gatherings yet at that time, so we are also working on a "PLAN B".

Again, this year's high school graduation is currently scheduled as follows:

Saturday, May 9th at 10:00 am
The Battlefield

SCHOOL CLOSURE UPDATE

Governor Doug Ducey and Superintendent of Public Instruction Kathy Hoffman announced earlier today that Arizona schools will remain closed through the end of the school year.

Mohave Accelerated will continue to provide online and packet-based instruction. The administration will be meeting this week to firm up our plans for alternate instruction and to address other issues like high school graduation.

Please be patient as we finalize our plans for the remainder of the year, but feel free to ask questions or share comments here. Above all, make sure your children are continuing to complete their school work... either online, or via the packets that can be picked up in the elementary and high school offices M-Th, 9am - 3pm.

https://azgovernor.gov/governor/news/2020/03/governor-ducey-superintendent-hoffman-announce-extension-school-closures
